#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:619
msgid "Performance Data (Raw)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:621
msgid "When using `Collectl` for hardware performance data, it is necessary to do the following before uploading the data to OSCAR.[^3]"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:623
msgid "[^3]: See Seiwert & Zaczyk 2021: p. 13 for details; see also Appendix A 2 on p. 46 for a Python script to automate some of these tasks."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:625
msgid "Remove all information above the header row."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:627
msgid "Remove all \\# characters from the file."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:629
msgid "In the first column, no separator value should come between the data-time (otherwise, the date and time will be interpreted as two separate columns)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:631
msgid "The date should also have a character inserted between YYYYMMDD, e.g., MM.DD.YYYY as above. Whatever character is used must be specified in `OSCAR`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:633
msgid "Column names can be anything you want as they will be specified within `OSCAR`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:635
msgid "The file must be saved in CSV format."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:637
msgid "Moreover, the hardware performance output from `Collectl` includes many columns that are not necessary for analysis. The only measurements that need to be specified are the following columns:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:639
msgid "[CPU]Totl = Processor"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:640
msgid "[MEM]Used = Main memory - used kilobytes"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:641
