#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:661
msgid "Uploading Data"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:663
msgid "Once the above CSV files are ready, you can run the analysis using OSCAR, which will generate a summary report you can use either for eco-certification or for your own data-driven purposes. In the `OSCAR` interface, note the following:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:665
msgid "The interface language is currently German only; see below for translations."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:667
msgid "The duration of the measurements in seconds must be specified."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:669
msgid "A semicolon separator is used."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:671
msgid "The correct formatting of the time stamp must be specified for each of the uploaded files, e.g.,`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%OS`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:673
msgid "Step 1: Obtain Measurement Data"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:675
msgid "The landing page of the website (below) states that the first step is obtaining measurement data (German: *Erfassung Messdaten*). If you are at this point in the process, you should have already measured your software and prepared the CSV files."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:677
msgid "![First obtain the measurement data (German: *Erfassung Messdaten*) in a laboratory.](images/sec3_oscar_1_landing.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:679
msgid "All examples here are based on the Okular data in [this ZIP file](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/feep/-/blob/master/measurements/okular/2022-09-22/2022-okular-data.zip)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:681
msgid "Step 2: Upload Measurement Data"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:683
msgid "Once you have the CSV files for the baseline, idle mode, and standard usage scenario measurements ready, click on *(2) Upload Messdaten* > *Upload*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:685
msgid "The measurement data (German: *Messdaten*) include the log file of actions (German: *Aktionen*), energy consumption (German: *Elektrische Leistung*), and hardware performance data (German: *Hardware-Auslastung*)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:687
msgid "Under *Messungen*, upload either the idle mode or standard usage scenario measurement data."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:689
msgid "For *Art der Messung* (‘Type of Measurement’) in the lower right of the UX, select *Leerlauf* (‘Idle Mode’) or *Nutzungsszenario* (‘Usage Scenario’) depending on which report you wish to generate."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:691
msgid "Under *Baselines* upload the baseline measurement data."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:693
msgid "Indicate the duration of the measurement scenarios in seconds (German: *Dauer der Einzelmessungen (s)*)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:695
msgid "Note that the baseline measurements are always uploaded along with either the idle mode or standard usage scenario measurements."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:697
msgid "See below for what a completed upload for the *Nutzungsszenario* looks like."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:699
msgid "![Uploading the measurement data (German: *Upload Messdaten*).](images/sec3_oscar_2_upload.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:701
msgid "***Timestamps*** &nbsp;&nbsp; Once the data has been uploaded, you will need to tell `OSCAR` how to read the data."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:703
msgid "Let’s start with the timestamp format (German: *Formatierung Zeitstempel*). This is one aspect of the process which can cause problems if not done correctly. This is done under *(2) Upload Messdaten* > *Formatierung Zeitstempel*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:705
msgid "Consider the Okular data:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:707
msgid "For the log file of actions, the datetime is encoded as *YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS* (e.g., \"2022-10-04 12:32:43.656\" in “okularActions.csv”)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:709
msgid "In `OSCAR`, this is specified as \"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%OS\" (see screenshot below). OSCAR will take care of the fractional seconds."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:711
msgid "For the energy consumption data, the datetime is encoded as *DD.MM.YY, HH:MM:SS* (e.g., \"04.10.22, 12:32:43\" in “okular_baseline_eletrLeistung.csv”). Note the period in the date and the comma seperating date from time, as well as only having two digits for the year."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:713
msgid "In `OSCAR` this is specified as \"%d.%m.%y, %H:%M:%OS\" (see screenshot below), in which the lowercase “%y” indicates a year with two digits."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:715
msgid "For the hardware performance data, the datetime is encoded as *DD.MM.YYYY HH:MM:SS* (e.g., \"04.10.2022 12:31:43\" in “baseline_hardware_formatiert.csv”). Note the period in the date and the four-digit year."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:717
msgid "In `OSCAR`, this is specified as: \"%d.%m.%Y %H:%M:%OS\" (see screenshot below), in which the uppercase “%Y” indicates a year with four digits."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:719
msgid "![Specifying the format of the timestamps (German: *Formatierung Zeitstempel*).](images/sec3_oscar_3_timestamp.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:721
msgid "***Measurement Data*** &nbsp;&nbsp; After the timestamps have been correctly specified, let’s explore the format of the measurement data (German: *Formatierung Messdaten*) in `OSCAR`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:723
msgid "First, take a look at the log file of actions (German: *Aktionen*). This is done under *(2) Upload Messdaten* > *Formatierung Messdaten* > *Aktionen*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:725
msgid "Here you need to indicate for the uploaded CSV file the separator (German: *Trennzeichen*), the string delimiter (German: *Textqualifizierer*), and the decimal separator (German: *Dezimaltrennzeichen*)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:727
msgid "For the Okular data, this is defined as a semi-colon separator, double quotation string delimiter, and a period or full-stop decimal separator (see screenshot below)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:729
msgid "Additionally, you will need to specify the following:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:731
msgid "whether the first line contains headings (German: *Erste Zeile enthält Überschriften*);"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:732
msgid "the number of lines to skip (German: *Anzahl zu überspringender Zeilen*); and"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:733
msgid "the character encoding (German: *Zeichensatz (Encoding)*)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:735
msgid "For the Okular data, this is defined as follows in the following screenshot: “first line contains headings” is unchecked, 0 lines are skipped, and character encoding is utf-8."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:737
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:747
msgid "When everything is defined correctly, a preview of the spreadsheet will be shown."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:739
msgid "![Specifying the format of the measurement data (German: *Formatierung Messdaten*) for the log file of actions (German: *Aktionen*).](images/sec3_oscar_4_actions.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:741
msgid "Second, take a look at the energy consumption measurements (German: *Elektrische Leistung*). This is done under *(2) Upload Messdaten* > *Formatierung Messdaten* > *Elektrische Leistung*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:743
msgid "The required input is the same as for the log file of actions, seen in the following screenshot."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:745
msgid "For the Okular data here, this is a semi-colon separator, double quotation string delimiter, and character encoding utf-8. However, now a comma is specified for the decimal separator and a checkmark indicates that the first line contains headings. Finally, the 1st line is skipped."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:749
msgid "![Specifying the format for the energy consumption data (German: *Elektrische Leistung*).](images/sec3_oscar_5_energy.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:751
msgid "Finally, take a look at the hardware performance data (German: *Hardware-Auslastung*). This is done under *(2) Upload Messdaten* > *Formatierung Messdaten* > *Hardware-Auslastung*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:753
msgid "The required input is the same. The input in this example is a semi-colon separator, a double quotation string delimiter, a period (a.k.a. full stop) decimal separator. There is a checkmark that the first line contains headings, 0 lines are skipped, and the character encoding is utf-8."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:755
msgid "However, now there is the additional requirement of specifying the columns (German: *Spalten*)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:757
msgid "For the columns specification, the following need to be identified; select NA for unused columns, e.g., “Auslastung Auslagerungsdatei” here."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:759
msgid "*Zeitstempel*: Datetime (i.e., ‘Date-Time’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:760
msgid "*CPU-Auslastung*: CPU (i.e., ‘X.CPU.Totl’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:761
msgid "*RAM-Auslastung*: RAM (i.e., ‘X.MEM.Used’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:762
msgid "*Über Netzwerk gesendet*: Network transmitted (i.e., ‘X.NET.TxKBTot’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:763
msgid "*Über Netzwerk empfangen*: Network received (i.e., ‘X.NET.RxKBTot’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:764
msgid "*Von Festplatte gelesen*: Disk read (i.e., ‘X.DSK.ReadKBTot’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:765
msgid "*Auf Festplatte geschrieben*: Disk written (i.e., ‘X.DSK.WriteKBTot’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:766
msgid "*Auslastung Auslagerungsdatei*: Swap (here, ‘N/A’)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:768
msgid "![Specifying the format for the hardware performance data (German: *Hardware-Auslastung*).](images/sec3_oscar_6_hw.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:770
msgid "Translations"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:772
msgid "Here is an overview of some of the German terminology used in `OSCAR` and the English translations:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:774
msgid "*Messungen*: Measurements (e.g., Idle Mode or SUS)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:775
msgid "*Aktionen*: Actions (i.e., log file of actions taken)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:776
msgid "*Elektrische Leistung*: ‘Electrical power’ (i.e., energy consumption measurements)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:777
msgid "*Hardware-Auslastung*: ‘Hardware load’ (i.e., hardware performance measurements)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:778
msgid "*Dauer der Einzelmessungen (s)*: ‘Duration of the individual measurements (s)’ (i.e., specify how long each iteration was in seconds)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:779
msgid "*Art der Messung*: ‘Type of measurement’"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:780
msgid "*Leerlauf*: ‘Idle’ (i.e., Idle mode)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:781
msgid "*Nutzungsszenario*: ‘Usage scenario’ (i.e., SUS)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:783
msgid "*Formatierung Messdaten*: ‘Formatting measurement data’"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:784
msgid "*Formatierung Zeitstempel*: ‘Formatting timestamp’"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:786
msgid "*Trennzeichen* ‘Separator’"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:787
msgid "*Textqualifizierer*: ‘String delimiter’"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:788
