#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1059
msgid "Many FOSS projects may take for granted that Free Software respects user autonomy and in some cases information from the above list is missing from websites, manuals, wikis, etc. This may include documentation about support for open standards, uninstallability, continuity of support, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1061
msgid "Documenting this information is important, both for fulfilling the Blue Angel award criteria and for giving users information about long-term sustainable use of their software and hardware."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1063
msgid "This is not an exhaustive presentation for each of the above categories of the Blue Angel criteria. Rather, this guide focuses on aspects of the criteria which KDE/FOSS projects can easily document and provide (which is already most of the work). For the full criteria, see Section 3.1.3 in the [basic award criteria](https://www.blauer-engel.de/en/productworld/resources-and-energy-efficient-software-products)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1065
msgid "2.1 Data Formats"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1067
msgid "The main information to include in documentation:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1069
msgid "Which (open) data formats are supported&mdash;with links to specifications, e.g., [PDF](https://www.iso.org/standard/51502.html)?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1071
msgid "Also of interest: Are there examples of other software products that process these data formats?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1073
msgid "For an example of the online documentation of supported data formats for Okular, visit [the Okular website](https://okular.kde.org/formats/)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1075
msgid "An example of documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in [Annex 4](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-4-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1078
msgid "2.2 Transparency Of The Software Product"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1080
msgid "When missing, provide links to documentation of the API, source code, and software license. For example, for KMail:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1082
msgid "[KDE PIM API documentation](https://api.kde.org/kdepim/index.html)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1084
msgid "[Source code](https://invent.kde.org/pim/kmail)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1086
msgid "[License](https://invent.kde.org/pim/kmail/-/blob/master/LICENSES)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1088
msgid "An example of documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in [Annex 5](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/kmail/de-uz-215-eng-annex-5-kmail.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1091
msgid "2.3 Continuity Of Support"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1093
msgid "Details about continuity of support to document include:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1095
msgid "Information about how long the software has been supported for (with links to release announcements)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1097
msgid "Release schedule and details (e.g., who maintains the software)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1099
msgid "Statement that updates are free of charge."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1101
msgid "Declaration on how the free and open source software license enables continuous support indefinitely."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1103
msgid "Information about whether and how functional and security updates may be installed separately."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1105
msgid "An example of Okular’s continuity of support documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in Section 3.1.3.3 of [Annex 6](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-6-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1107
msgid "2.4 Uninstallability"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1109
msgid "How are users able to completely uninstall the software? Relevant details might include:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1111
msgid "Uninstallation instructions that depend on how the software was installed (source code or binary)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1113
msgid "Examples of uninstallation instructions (source code or package managers, with relevant links to documentation)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1115
msgid "Information about whether user-generated data is also removed when uninstalling a program."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1117
msgid "An example of Okular’s uninstallability documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in Section 3.1.3.4 of [Annex 6](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-6-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1119
msgid "2.5 Offline Capability"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1121
msgid "Does the software require external connections such as a license server in order to run? If not, and no network connection is needed as the software can be used offline, this should be documented."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1123
msgid "An example of Okular’s offline capability documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in Section 3.1.3.5 of [Annex 6](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-6-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1125
msgid "2.6 Modularity"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1127
msgid "Information to document includes:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1129
msgid "What aspects of the software are modular and can be deactivated during installation?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1131
msgid "Can the software manuals or translations be installed separately?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1133
msgid "Are any modules which are unrelated to the core functionality included with installation, such as tracking modules or cloud integration? If not, document it!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1135
msgid "An example of Okular’s modularity documentation for the Blue Angel can be found in Section 3.1.3.6 of [Annex 6](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-6-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1137
msgid "2.7 Freedom From Advertising"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1139
msgid "If the software does not display advertising, make this explicit in manuals and wikis and declare it in the Blue Angel application document."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1141
msgid "2.8 Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1143
msgid "This includes the following:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1145
msgid "General process for installing/uninstalling the software? This may include generic instructions or tutorials for a specific desktop environment or package manager."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1147
msgid "Data import/export process?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1149
msgid "What can users do to reduce the use of resources (e.g., configuration options for improving performance)?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1151
msgid "Does the software have any resource-intensive functionality not necessary for the core functionality? If not, great. Let’s tell the users!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1153
msgid "Licensing terms related to further development of the software products, with links to source code and license?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1155
msgid "Who supports the development of the software?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1157
msgid "Does the software collect any personal data? Is is compliant with existing data protection laws? If yes, document it!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1159
msgid "What is the privacy policy? Is there telemetry? If yes, how does the software handle data security, data collection, and data transmission? Also, are there ads or tracking embedded in the software? If not, excellent&mdash;now make sure to spread the word!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1161
msgid "An example of Okular’s product documentation for Blue Angel certification can be found in Section 3.1.3.8 of [Annex 6](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application/-/blob/master/applications/okular/de-uz-215-eng-annex-6-okular.md)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1163
msgid "Submitting To RAL"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1165
msgid "For examples of all of the above documentation, see KDE’s [Blue Angel Applications](https://invent.kde.org/teams/eco/blue-angel-application) repository."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1167
msgid "Once you have all of the documentation prepared, you need to submit it for review to RAL gGmbH (if you recall, RAL is the authorized body that assesses compliance with the award criteria). The portal for submitting Blue Angel applications can be found [here](https://portal.ral-umwelt.de/) (https://portal.ral-umwelt.de/)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/be4foss-handbook/handbook_web.md:1169
msgid "If you need help with the online interface, RAL provides [documentation](https://portal.ral-umwelt.de/RALUmwelt/Anleitung/1)."
