#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:9
msgid "In 2020, the German Environment Agency (German: *Umweltbundesamt*) released the award criteria for eco-certifying desktop software with the Blue Angel ecolabel (German: *Blauer Engel*). From 2021–2022, the BE4FOSS project under KDE Eco worked to advance eco-certification for resource and energy-efficient software in FOSS communities. Obtaining the Blue Angel ecolabel occurs in 3 steps: (1) Measure, (2) Analyze, and (3) Certify."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:11
msgid "Benefits of obtaining the Blue Angel ecolabel include:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:12
msgid "Recognition of reaching high standards for environmentally-friendly software design,"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:13
msgid "Differentiating free software from the alternatives,"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:14
msgid "Increasing the appeal of adoption for consumers, and"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:15
msgid "Promoting transparency in the ecological footprint of software."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:17
msgid "Learn more in the KDE Eco handbook “[Applying The Blue Angel Criteria To Free Software](https://eco.kde.org/handbook/)”."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/BE4FOSS/_index.md:0
msgid "Eco Label"
msgstr ""

